  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: In group chat, when `/send` is clicked a user may not select a recipient but still be able to proceed to next step (specify amount). He then ends up in a state where tapping on the send button does nothing because the recipient was not provided: \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36605458-11df5e1a-18c1-11e8-8b36-68b889cd121b.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\nMaybe in this case the send button should be disabled until user selects or types the recipient? @denis-sharypin wdyt? \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open a group chat\r\n- Type `/send`\r\n- Click the send button without providing the recipient\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, Feb 23\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n",
